  <preface id="preface">
    <title>Preface</title>
    <para>Welcome to the &agenti; Administrator Guide!</para>
    <para>This document describes how to configure and manage &agenti;. Background information for
      the technology and concepts used by the product is also discussed.</para>
    <section>
      <title>Summary of contents</title>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_intro"/> describes the main functionality and purpose of &abbrev;.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_install"/> describes how to install the &agentabbrev; in various scenarios and how to upgrade to new versions.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_configuration_audjrn"/> provides detailed description on configuring &agentabbrev; security audit journaling.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_configuration"/> provides detailed description on configuring and managing &agenti;.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_sendtosyslog"/> describes the Send To Syslog command.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_sendtoceflog"/> describes the Send To CEF log command.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_allsyslog"/> describes the procedure ALLSysLog.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_allceflog"/> describes the procedure ALLCefLog.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_configuringservers"/> describes the procedure of configuring &agentabbrev; Servers.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="chapter_ibm_troubleshooting"/> describes how to solve common errors and problems.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="app_ibm_qaudjrn"/> includes the text of the End-User License Agreement applicable to &agenti;.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="app_eula"/> includes the text of the End-User License Agreement applicable to &agenti;.</para>
      <para><xref linkend="syslog-ng_glossary"/> provides definitions of important terms used in this guide.</para>
      <!-- <para><xref linkend="ix01"/> provides cross-references to important terms used in this guide.</para>-->
    </section>
